external_knowledge:
- Major global players refer to companies with a significant market presence, typically those with high market capitalizations;
- Keen analysts are those who closely monitor and evaluate a company for investment purposes;
- Half-trillion-dollar mark refers to a market cap over $500 billion.

- Gardens metaphorically represent watchlists; 
- Plants refer to items within the watchlists;
- Gardeners are the users who own the watchlists;
- Contact details are the email addresses of the users.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT c.security_name, c.ticker
FROM companies c
JOIN news_feeds n ON c.company_id = n.company_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'major financial giants' refers to companies in the financial services industry with notable market presence;
- 'under the helm of Larry Fink' means companies where Larry Fink is the CEO;
- 'market worth' refers to the market capitalization;
- 'average fluctuation in stock prices and percentages' refers to the average change amount and average change percentage of their stock prices.
